The paper discusses the decision boundary of deep neural networks, which is a fundamental topic in machine learning. The paper also investigates the convergence of the last weight layer of a neural network to a linear SVM, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper's focus on understanding deep learning models and techniques suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's discussion of practical problems of deep learning, such as catastrophic forgetting and adversarial attacking, suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
